Got Windows?

In the directory C:\Windows\system\fonts you can find various interesting fonts.
Copy these files from the windows partition in this directory:

	arialbd.ttf, arialbi.ttf, ariali.ttf, arial.ttf,
	courbd.ttf, courbi.ttf couri.ttf, cour.ttf,
	timesbd.ttf, timesbi.ttf, timesi.ttf, times.ttf

Also, interesting are these ones:

	ariblk.ttf,
	georgiab.ttf, georgiai.ttf, georgia.ttf, georgiaz.ttf,
	lucon.ttf,
	verdanab.ttf, verdanai.ttf, verdana.ttf, verdanaz.ttf,

There are ready symbolic links for {sans|serif|mono}-{regular|bold|italic|bolditalic}
for using these fonts for the pyvm GUI/web browser.

At the moment, this is the best way to see international text in pyvm's web browser.
(fonts tested with XP)
